Trails, Transit, and Tracts

This map allows readers to explore the county trails of San Luis Obispo County in relation to the the locations of transit stops and census-tract-level median incomes. It shows that, for the most part, county trails are not accessible by public transit.

The intended audience for this map is a resident of San Luis Obispo County who might appreciate the ability to interactively explore the trails and transit stops that serve the places where they live, work, and recreate.

Date Sources:

  • Estimated median income from the 2019 American Community Survey (5-year sample), accessed via tidycensus package
  • Trail data from San Luis Opispo County Open Data
  • SLO Transit stop data from the SLO Transit GTFS feed
  • RTA transit stop data from the RTA GTFS feed
